<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >i.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> On CasualLeave, SCL,CCL</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be treated as OFF duty after Odd Hrs and can be booked after 08:00 Hrs,
        (BRC divn it is 00:00 Hrs also some divn it may be 06:00 hrs)</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >1% of basic pay and 7.26 Hrsper day of the leave period.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >ii.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> On LAP</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be treated as Available after Odd Hrs and be booked first on turn.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >1% of basic pay and 7.26 Hrsper day of the leave period.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >iii.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> Commuted Sick Leave. LHAP</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be treated as Available at odd Hrs for AN and 12 hrs for
        BN. AN/BN shall be as per the medical memo.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >1% of basic pay and 7.26 Hrsper day of the leave period.</td>
</tr>


<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >iv.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> IOD</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be treated as Available at odd Hrs for AN and 12 hrs for
        BN. AN/BN shall be as per the medical memo. Except no leave is debited from the employee</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >1% of basic pay and 7.26 Hrsper day of the leave period.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >v.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> Absent, Leave not due</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be treated as Available after Odd Hrs next day in case he
        comes to duty after 12:01 Hrs. If he comes before 12:00 Hrs then Same day Odd Hrs on duty.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >No Payment, mileage, RA or Hrs for the day.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >vi.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> PME</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be treated as Available at next day odd Hrs for AN and
        12:00 hrs for BN. AN/BN shall be as per the medical memo.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >1% of basic pay and 7.26 Hrs per day of the leave period.
        If reports to duty BN then no Running allowance credit is there</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >vii.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> Maternity,Paternity Leave</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be treated as Available at odd Hrs</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >1% of basic pay and 7.26 Hrs per day of the leave period.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >viii.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> Training.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall do OFF duty at crew booking point and there after be
        given standard (Standard rest are variable) rest after he can be booked. Max rest is 16 Hrs</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >Shall be paid 7.26 Hrs for the training period and OSRA of
        160 kms for outstation and 1% RA for HQ cases.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >ix.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> Enquiry</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall do OFF duty at crew booking point and after given rest
        as per normal train running shall be booked. Journey period is as per Releasing letter.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >OSRA paid out of HQ. And for the Journey period shall be
        treated as TAP. Or 1 % of basic pay at HQ And 7.26 Hrs of duty.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >x.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> Special Duty for< 30 days</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall do OFF duty at crew booking point and after given 16
            Hrs rest he can be booked.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >OSRA paid out of HQ. Or 1 % of basic pay at HQ and 7.26 Hrs of duty.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >xi.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC">Learning road,Handling</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be as per normal duty</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >Actual as earned during LR and 7.26 Hrs of duty.</td>
</tr>

<tr>
	<td style="color: #9900CC" >xii.</td>
	<td style="color: #9900CC"> Under Suspension.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC"> Shall be treated as Available as soon as revoked.</td>
        <td style="color: #9900CC" >Normally however for the day of revoking he shall be given
        actual running allowance for the journey only.</td>
</tr>

